page_title: 'Use Azure OpenAI Service with large datasets'
page_description: Learn how to integrate Azure OpenAI Service with SynapseML and Apache Spark to apply large language models at a distributed scale.
chunk_content: Prerequisites- An Azure subscription. Create one for free.- An Azure OpenAI resource. Create a resource.- An Apache Spark cluster with SynapseML installed. - Create a serverless Apache Spark pool. - To install SynapseML for your Apache Spark cluster, see Install SynapseML.> [!NOTE]> The `OpenAICompletion()` transformer is designed to work with the Azure OpenAI Service legacy models like `Text-Davinci-003`, which supports prompt-based completions. Newer models like the current `GPT-3.5 Turbo` and `GPT-4` model series are designed to work with the new chat completion API that expects a specially formatted array of messages as input. If you working with embeddings or chat completion models, please check the Chat Completion and Generating Text Embeddings sections bellow.> > The Azure OpenAI SynapseML integration supports the latest models via the OpenAIChatCompletion() transformer.We recommend that you create an Azure Synapse workspace. However, you can also use Azure Databricks, Azure HDInsight, Spark on Kubernetes, or the Python environment with the `pyspark` package.
